close_reason: "ADR formalized and accepted: the profile lint severity model (errors break apply / silently lose data; warnings flag structurally-valid suspicious cross-references; assertProjectProfile throws on errors, strict also on warnings) is recorded in the item body and implemented in src/core/profile/profile-lint.ts as shipped in PR #404."
body: "## ADR: Profile lint severity model\n\n### Status\nAccepted — implemented in PR #404 (`src/core/profile/profile-lint.ts`), exercised by `assertProjectProfile` and `pm profile lint`.\n\n### Context\n`lintProjectProfile` grades findings so that `pm profile apply` never silently loses data and authors get early signal on suspicious-but-valid content. A single severity would either block valid layered setups (false positives) or let data-loss conditions through.\n\n### Decision\n- **Errors** are conditions that make `pm profile apply` throw or silently drop data: invalid/empty type, status, or field (normalizer throws on empty id, builtin-status override, builtin-field shadow); duplicate normalized keys within a dimension (silent last-wins upsert); unknown/invalid config knob (planConfig throws at apply); empty profile name (resolution requires it); malformed workflow transition pairs (silently dropped by resolveTypeWorkflows).\n- **Warnings** are structurally valid but likely-bug content: a workflow `type` neither builtin nor profile-declared; workflow transitions referencing a status token neither builtin nor profile-declared (dead/unreachable rule); a template `options.type` referencing an undeclared type; a non-normalized profile name; empty title/summary; empty package spec. Cross-references are warnings (not errors) because the target type/status may pre-exist in the tracker independent of the profile, so erroring would create false positives against valid layered setups.\n- `assertProjectProfile` throws on `errorCount > 0` by default; `strict: true` also throws on warnings for CI gates.\n\n### Consequences\nApply-breaking and data-loss conditions are caught at author time with stable codes, while layered/extension setups are not falsely rejected; `strict` mode gives CI a zero-warning bar. Implemented and covered at 100% in #404."
